==Discussion==

Our final design was chosen using a delphi process and was seen to best meet the client's criteria. The design fully provided enough light to cover the trail during the night. The 10 lights from Cooper Industries are charged with a photovoltaic charging system. The photovoltaic system is how the design met the criterion of appropriateness of the material used, as well as fitting the clients specification of an off-grid energy source for the lights. The design leveraged local resources by using upcycled wood and re-used freezer panels from Safeway in the shed construction process. To meet the safety criterion, all the electrical components of the system are locked in the shed, where only workers and volunteers from the Friends of The Dunes can reach them. The system is also grounded to a steel bar buried under the shed to protect anyone from potential shock risks.

